{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"210c4477-68fb-40fe-a1f0-30e40df6b8de","content":"Good news — with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` natively uses the Microsoft.Testing.Platform protocol. **You no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`** — that property was the opt-in bridge for .NET 9 and earlier. Keep `EnableMSTestRunner` since it builds your test project as an MTP executable.\n\nHere's the fix:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_011mSFxnc49QNH4MuD46uqmZ","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01871skV52T6wXbz6z54XdvV","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-5e6fa985eb704ec4ae9d3dae8d98b885/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-5e6fa985eb704ec4ae9d3dae8d98b885/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"4762df7b-f50a-4106-8591-63eabe9ec387","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK and wants to know about Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) support. Let me provide accurate information.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` has native support for Microsoft.Testing.Platform. The key changes:\n\n1. .NET 10 SDK's `dotnet test` natively speaks the MTP protocol, so `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is no longer needed — it was a bridge/opt-in property for .NET 9 and earlier SDKs.\n2. You still need `EnableMSTestRunner` to build the test project as an executable that uses MTP.\n\n\n3. Since .NET 10 handles MTP natively, I can remove the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property from their project file.","outputTokens":518,"requestId":"0830:1DCDBF:7D4C40B:8B8E591:69EABF2D"},"id":"b255bb3c-5096-44f2-aa42-969a2655a638","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:54:14.401Z","parentId":"835be96b-1638-480c-ba1f-2d06274a0791"}
